body:
Repro steps:
1. Open some flutter app in IJ
2. Start a debugging session
3. Press hot reload button

Actual and expected: A small status update (`Reloaded 1 of ...`) is printed in the console.
1. Press restart ('Full Application Restart') button

Expected: A similar status update (`Restart performed in xxx ms.`) is printed
Actual: Nothing at all is printed to the console

comment_data.body: Tagging 0.1 as this is what lead me to #332
@stevemessick : is this on our side or is there a missing notification from the daemon?

This is working as designed. There is no console output from the daemon for a Restart. Doing a Hot Reload will print a line displaying the number of libraries that got reloaded. Eventually, it also displays how much time the reload took, but currently that's kinda broken -- it isn't emitted until after the next event and so the reload times are quite ludicrously long. See https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/6400 for a description of the intermittent problem I discovered.

We could add an artificial log message if that would help. Or we could get the daemon maintainers to add logging for restart.

> We could add an artificial log message if that would help. Or we could get the daemon maintainers to add logging for restart.

@mit-mit : what do you think?
Sounds like this would be a pretty easy fix in the daemon? If not, lets as the artificial message on our side.

One additional inconsistency: If you to both reload and starts when not debugging (which is possible using keyboard shortcuts), then you get a message saying the app is not running _only_ for reload. I find that odd, as this message is coming from the plugin, not the daemon:

[RestartFlutterAppKeyAction.java](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/blob/c943c8248808967d4b3c01b978c0677caf39bbc3/src/io/flutter/actions/RestartFlutterAppKeyAction.java)
[HotReloadFlutterAppKeyAction.java](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/blob/c943c8248808967d4b3c01b978c0677caf39bbc3/src/io/flutter/actions/HotReloadFlutterAppKeyAction.java)

title: Missing console output when doing a Restart
